<!--
Greek (Greece) translation — full UI coverage. εσύ-form (2nd-person
singular familiar) throughout: "Πάτησε", "Όρισε", "Φόρεσε", "Πάρε".
That's the standard Greek app register for a casual / spousal-tone
brand. The plural / formal-polite εσείς-form ("Πατήστε", "Ορίστε")
isn't used here — it reads as institutional in modern Android UI and
doesn't fit the existing prose voice ("Δικός σου ClothesCast", "Τι
να φορέσεις σήμερα").

Brand name "ClothesCast" stays in Latin script, as do all third-party
brand names (Gemini, OpenAI, ElevenLabs, Open-Meteo, Android Keystore,
GitHub, dontkillmyapp.com) and the URLs.

Quotation marks around nested toggle / event labels use Greek
guillemets «…» — locale-native style, the same convention Greek
publications and apps follow (NOT the German „…" low-high pair the
Romance / Germanic locales use here).

What is NOT overridden, by design:
- `app_name` — brand identifier, identical across locales.
- `insight_time_am` / `_pm` / `_midnight` / `_noon` (and *_minutes
  variants) — English-only spoken-time formatter helpers. Greek uses
  `insight_time_hour` / `_hour_minutes` ("15:00" / "15:30") which are
  translated below; the AM/PM keys exist for the
  `Locale.language == "en"` path only and would never be read in an
  el-GR runtime.

Picker labels under `settings_region_language_*` and
`settings_tts_voice_locale_*` give the Greek names for every offered
locale (Αγγλικά (Ηνωμένες Πολιτείες), Γαλλικά (Καναδάς), Κινέζικα
(απλοποιημένα), …). The locale tag stored on disk (en-US / fr-CA /
zh-CN) is unchanged; only the displayed label localizes.
-->
